ğŸ”’ Security Features
Authentication: Laravel Sanctum with JWT

Authorization: User-specific task access

Input Validation: Server-side validation

Password Hashing: Bcrypt encryption

CORS Protection: Configured for frontend domain

CSRF Protection: Laravel built-in protection
---

ğŸ“± Responsive Design
Mobile-first approach

Tailwind CSS utility classes

Breakpoints for all device sizes

Accessible form controls
---

ğŸš¨ Error Handling
Frontend
Loading states with spinners

Error messages with toast notifications

Form validation errors

Network error handling

Backend
HTTP status codes

Validation error responses

Authentication middleware

Model not found exceptions
---

ğŸ“Š Database Schema
Users Table:
id (primary key)

name (string)

email (string, unique)

password (hashed)

created_at, updated_at

Tasks Table:
id (primary key)

user_id (foreign key)

title (string)

description (text, nullable)

status (enum: pending, in_progress, done)

created_at, updated_at
---

ğŸ”„ Development Workflow
Setup: Clone repo and run docker-compose up

Development: Code changes auto-refresh

Testing: Run tests before commits

Build: Production build with npm run build and composer install --optimize

---
ğŸ› Troubleshooting
Common Issues:
Port already in use:
bash
# Change ports in .env files
# Or kill processes on ports 3000/8000
Database connection errors:
Check SQLite file permissions

Verify database path in .env

Run migrations: php artisan migrate

CORS errors:
Verify SANCTUM_STATEFUL_DOMAINS in .env

Check frontend API URL configuration

Docker issues:
bash
# Rebuild containers
docker-compose down
docker-compose build --no-cache
docker-compose up
---
ğŸ“ Assumptions & Notes
Development Focus: SQLite used for simplicity in development

Authentication: JWT tokens stored in localStorage (for demo purposes)

Security: In production, implement refresh tokens and secure storage

Scalability: Current implementation suitable for small-medium applications

UI/UX: Basic but functional interface; can be enhanced with more time
